like carbon capture or a new generation of nuclear power plants to new batteries that revolutionize

08:06.900 --> 08:15.140
the energy storage from renewables. But innovation takes time, years and decades, and we don't have

08:15.140 --> 08:21.740
this time. Every year, we keep adding more carbon to the atmosphere. This means we can't keep relying

08:21.740 --> 08:27.780
on innovation alone. We need to find ways to reduce emissions today while we invent what we

08:27.780 --> 08:33.500
will need in the future. The less fossil fuel we burn over the next few years, the more time we

08:33.500 --> 08:39.420
give innovation to catch up. The more low-carbon energy infrastructure we build today, the more we

